# Your Credentials -- What You Have Access To

This file explains every API key and service credential in your `.env` file.
If a key is not listed here, you do not have access to it. Ask Thanh if you need something new.

## How Credentials Work

Your API keys live in a file called `.env` at the root of your workspace. Claude Code loads this file automatically. You should never need to copy-paste keys manually.

**Important:** The `.env` file must NEVER be committed to GitHub. There is a pre-commit hook that will block it, but treat this as a habit, not a safety net.

---

## GREEN -- Ready to Use (pre-filled in your .env)

These are already in your `.env` file and safe to use immediately.

### Recraft V4 (Image Generation)
- **Variable:** `RECRAFT_API_KEY`
- **What it does:** Generates SVG vector images and raster images from text prompts
- **Cost:** ~$0.04 per raster image, ~$0.08 per vector
- **Example use:** `Ask Claude: "Generate a hero image for an MSP website using Recraft"`
- **Useful for:** Design bounties, GBP image sets, social media visuals

### Groq (Voice Transcription)
- **Variable:** `GROQ_API_KEY`
- **What it does:** Transcribes audio files to text using Whisper (very fast)
- **Cost:** Free tier is generous -- you are unlikely to exceed it
- **Example use:** `Ask Claude: "Transcribe this audio file using Groq"`
- **Useful for:** Any bounty that processes voice recordings or meeting audio

### Google Stitch (AI Design Generation)
- **Variable:** `GOOGLE_STITCH_API_KEY`
- **What it does:** Generates UI designs and layouts from text descriptions
- **Cost:** Free beta -- 350 standard + 200 pro generations per month
- **Example use:** `Ask Claude: "Generate a dashboard layout using Google Stitch"`
- **Useful for:** Design bounties, rapid UI prototyping

### Screenshot Service
- **Variables:** `SCREENSHOT_ENDPOINT` + `SCREENSHOT_AUTH_TOKEN`
- **What it does:** Takes full-page screenshots of any URL (hosted Playwright service)
- **Cost:** Negligible (runs on Vercel hobby tier)
- **Example use:** `Ask Claude: "Take a screenshot of https://example.com"`
- **Useful for:** QA bounties, before/after comparisons, design reference captures

### Discord Webhook
- **Variable:** `DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL`
- **What it does:** Posts messages to the `#level-up` Discord channel
- **Cost:** Free
- **Example use:** `Ask Claude: "Post a build update to Discord"`
- **Useful for:** Notifications, build status updates, demo sharing

### Supabase Sandbox (Your Database)
- **Variables:** `SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- **What it does:** Your playground database. Create tables, store data, run queries
- **Cost:** Free (Supabase free tier)
- **Important:** This is the `level-up-sandbox` project. Never connect to any other Supabase project.
- **Example use:** `Ask Claude: "Create a table called client_profiles in Supabase"`

### Anthropic Claude API
- **Variable:** `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
- **What it does:** Powers Claude AI calls from your code (not the same as Claude Code itself)
- **Cost:** Varies by model -- your key has a spending cap (ask Thanh for your limit)
- **Important:** This is an event-scoped key with a budget cap. Do not share it.
- **Example use:** Used automatically when your code calls the Claude API

### n8n Base URL
- **Variable:** `N8N_BASE_URL`
- **What it does:** Points to the MSP Launchpad n8n automation platform
- **Note:** This is just the URL (https://msplaunchpad.app.n8n.cloud). You do NOT have the API key by default. If your bounty needs n8n API access, ask Thanh.

